==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incult
<hw>In*cult"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>incultus</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>cultus</ets>, p. p.
of <ets>colere</ets> to cultivate: cf. F. <ets>inculte</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Untilled; uncultivated; crude; rude; uncivilized.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Germany then, says Tacitus, was <qex>incult</qex> and horrid, now
full of magnificent cities.</q> <rj><qau>Burton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His style is diffuse and <qex>incult</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>M. W.
Shelley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incultivated</ent>⟦br⟧
